cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new optimization algorithm for training deep neural networks. It may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) for the same reason. Additionally, since the paper discusses empirical results on common machine learning problems, it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
